# Proposed Architecture - AFTER Hardening
## Meridian FinServe Hardened Network Segment

### Hardening Changes (Directly Addressing Findings):

| Layer | Control | Implementation | Effort | Trade-off |
|-------|---------|----------------|--------|-----------|
| Perimeter | Egress filtering (allow-list only) | S | Blocks all unknown outbound |
| Perimeter | DNS filtering (block malicious domains) | S | May block legitimate new domains |
| Segmentation | Micro-segmentation (DMZ/App/Data tiers) | M | Increased firewall rules complexity |
| Application | TLS inspection (decrypt at perimeter) | M | Performance overhead, privacy concerns |
| Identity | MFA for all internal access | M | User friction |
| Data | DLP solution for outbound data | L | Cost, potential false positives |
| Observability | NSM + SIEM with baseline alerting | M | Storage costs, staffing needs |

